    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - REMOVE - REMOTE CONTROL (Figure 3 )</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>REMOTE CONTROL (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302303">Figure 3</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1302303" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302303" filename="../figg13/g1302303.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3. Remote Control - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six bolts. Separate the remote control from the transmission.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the tie rod from the housing and the selection lever.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the selection lever from the outer shift lever.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts from the outer shift lever. Tap the lever off the shift rod.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut the tie straps from the boot and remove it.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shift finger bolts and tap the finger off the rod.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the rod from the housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To disassemble the selection lever subassembly, first remove the snap ring and retainer
                plate.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The bearing race, ball stud, and a final bearing race are removed next.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two springs and the boot.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
